description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Healthcare Support Worker Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Team - Wilton &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours/ Week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wilton Community Team has a Band 3 Health Care Support Worker vacancy. We wish to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;recruit an enthusiastic individual to work within the therapy team.Ideally this would be someone who has previous experience working with people in a community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The therapy team work predominately with patients in their own homes completing assessments and treatment interventions to enable the individual to gain their optimum level of function and independence, offering support and guidance if on-going care is required from other available services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will need to have a good general education and an NVQ Level 3 in Health Care is an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full driving licence and access to a vehicle is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are excited at the prospect of working in this challenging yet highly rewarding area of healthcare then we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wiltshire Health and Care are supportive of their staffs’ wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic and innovative staffs, which are required to work seamlessly with multi-professional community services and forge close links with other local teams including Primary Care and Salisbury Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquires regarding this exciting opportunity please call Beth Palmer on 07771 872431 or 01722 746776&lt;/p&gt;
